   "body" : "I have client 0.11.2 (32-bit Linux, fresh download). I'm reindexing after a crash, or re-importing the blcokchain, doesn't matter.\r\nThe problem: at first it zipped along quite fast, but now I'm at block 300000 and it takes 3sec to process a single block.\r\n\r\nIf this slowdown continues I expect the full blockchain to be imported some time after the sun blows up in a couple billion years, so I assume there must be a  problem somewhere.\r\n\r\nI found one strange message in the debug log:\r\n```\r\n2016-01-01 18:49:20 Leaving block file 133: CBlockFileInfo(blocks=0, size=0, heights=0...0, time=1970-01-01...1970-01-01\r\n```\r\nno idea whether that's related to my problem.",
